<@UJHD6A81H> I thought I had explained myself the other day.
*The mod_harbour code and the Javascript code run in completely separate contexts.*
*Unless you explicitly pass things in requests, mod_harbour has NO access to any javascript functions or variables.*

If you truly need to get variables from javascript to the server, you load a new page (passing the js value through url parameters or through a form) or you use ajax (effectively loading a new page in the background) and parse those values from mod_harbour.
If what you need is for harbour to run inside the browser, take a look at <#CN5QSU3DL|harbour_emscripten> instead
